&lt;p&gt;Is there a simple way to convert one date format into another date format in PHP?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-php s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-php&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable&quot;&gt;$old_date&lt;/span&gt; = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_ invoke__&quot;&gt;date&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;y-m-d-h-i-s&apos;&lt;/span&gt;);            &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// works&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable&quot;&gt;$middle&lt;/span&gt; = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_ invoke__&quot;&gt;strtotime&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable&quot;&gt;$old_date&lt;/span&gt;);             &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// returns bool(false)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable&quot;&gt;$new_date&lt;/span&gt; = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_ invoke__&quot;&gt;date&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;Y-m-d H:i:s&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable&quot;&gt;$middle&lt;/span&gt;);   &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// returns 1970-01-01 00:00:00&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But I&apos;d of course like it to return a current date rather than the crack &apos;o dawn. What am I doing wrong?&lt;/p&gt;
